# Iframe scrolling — LOCKED, ask the user before ANY edit

The iframe scrolling system (desktop wheel forwarding + mobile internal
scroll + live mode switching for the Shopify theme editor's mobile-preview
toggle) is **working and verified** as of `ai-art-studio-189` (2026-07-04)
after many failed iterations. The user has explicitly required that it not be
modified without their approval.

## Hard rules

1. **Before editing ANY of the locked parts below, STOP and ask the user for
   explicit approval first** — even for "small" or "obviously safe" changes,
   refactors, or drive-by cleanups. Describe what you want to change and why,
   and wait for their go-ahead.
2. Read `docs/iframe-scroll-architecture.md` in full before proposing a change.
   Every non-obvious rule in there fixed a real production bug (e.g. all scroll
   writes must use `appaiInstantScrollBy` because themes set CSS
   `scroll-behavior: smooth`, which silently freezes plain `scrollTop` writes;
   `mobileNativeScroll` can change LIVE after mount via the theme editor's
   mobile-preview toggle, so it must never be treated as a value fixed once at
   mount).
3. After ANY approved change, run all four verification scripts against the
   live dev store and check the pass criteria in the doc:
   `npx tsx scripts/diagnose-scroll.ts`, `npx tsx scripts/diagnose-savor.ts`,
   `npx tsx scripts/diagnose-mobile.ts`, `npx tsx scripts/diagnose-resize.ts`.
4. **If any verification fails, revert immediately and redeploy** (Railway
   `production` push + `npx shopify app deploy -f`). Do not iterate forward on
   a broken state.

## Locked parts

- `extensions/theme-extension/assets/appai-art-embed.js`:
  `appaiInstantScrollBy`, `appaiAnimateWheelScroll`, `appaiScrollParentPage`,
  `appaiGetPageScrollElement`, `appaiScrollRootForEmbedIframe`,
  `appaiCanScroll`, `appaiAttachIframeWheelForward`, `appaiIsMobileScrollMode`,
  the wheel-attach calls in `cleanupDuplicateGenerators`, the
  `resize`/`wheel`/`touchscroll`/`touchfling`/`touchcancel`/`set-scroll-mode`
  message handlers, `mobileNativeScroll` detection, `applyMobileNativeScrollFrame`,
  `clearMobileNativeScrollFrame`, and the `matchMedia(...).addEventListener('change', ...)`
  live mode-switch block.
- `client/src/pages/embed-design.tsx`: `mobileNativeScroll` state and its
  `set-scroll-mode` message handler, the resize-report effect, the
  wheel-forward effect (incl. the `__APPAI_PARENT_WHEEL_FORWARD__` dedupe
  check and the mobile boundary hand-off / explicit `scrollBy`), both
  touch-scroll effects.
- `client/src/index.css`: all `html[data-appai-embed]` scroll / overflow /
  scrollbar rules.
- `server/routes.ts`: the script tags injected by `buildCustomizerBootHtml()`.
